❗️CLOSED❗️
Every day that I wake up, I know that I have a warm house, a full belly, family and friends that love me, a paying job, a car that runs, clean water, and clothes on my back. To have all of these things makes me an extremely fortunate person. Unfortunately, many children and families around us cannot say the same thing.

My sister Shannon and I knew that we wanted to team up, combine our resources and do a fundraiser this year to help give back to our community. As born and raised New Mexicans, we knew we wanted to pick an organization close to home and close to our hearts, which is why Cuidando Los Niños was the perfect choice. They provide much needed levels of support and aid to the homeless children and families in our community. 

Our fundraiser will run 12/4-12/18, giving us enough time to shop for clothing, food, toys, housing & cleaning supplies, and hygienic necessities, as well as time to drop everything off directly to the organization before the holidays. 

We thank you so much for your support, sharing and donations - all of which will help to achieve our goal of $750. And as an extra thank you, anyone who donates $40+ will get a free fundraiser shirt! 

We look forward to taking you along with us throughout the whole process 🤍
